---
import ArticleLayout from '../../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Agents, scripts, CI — Git Treeline"
  description="MCP with full read/write tools, JSON flags, gtl resolve, and structured status output for agent automation."
  canonical="https://git-treeline.dev/use-cases/agents-automation/"
  breadcrumb="Use cases"
  breadcrumbHref="/use-cases/"
  heading="Agents provision worktrees, not just query them"
>
  <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-400 mb-10 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
    The MCP server exposes the full GTL toolset: create worktrees, allocate resources, wire up cross-repo dependencies, and control the dev server. AI agents work with real allocations instead of guessing ports and parsing stdout.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-4 scroll-mt-24 text-balance mt-14">MCP: first-class automation interface</h2>
  <p class="text-muted mb-4">
    <code class="text-accent-light">gtl mcp</code> starts the Model Context Protocol server. Agents in Cursor, Claude Code, Windsurf, and other MCP-compatible editors call tools directly instead of parsing shell output.
  </p>
  <ul class="text-muted space-y-3 mb-8">
    <li><strong class="text-white">Provisioning</strong> — <code class="text-accent-light">new</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">setup</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">link</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">unlink</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">env_sync</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">config_set</code></li>
    <li><strong class="text-white">Query</strong> — <code class="text-accent-light">status</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">list</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">port</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">routes</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">resolve</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">env</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">where</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">doctor</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">db_name</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">config_get</code></li>
    <li><strong class="text-white">Supervisor</strong> — <code class="text-accent-light">start</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">stop</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">restart</code></li>
    <li><strong class="text-white">Resources</strong> — <code class="text-accent-light">gtl://allocations</code>, <code class="text-accent-light">gtl://config/user</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-4 scroll-mt-24 text-balance mt-14">JSON flags for shell-only agents</h2>
  <ul class="text-muted space-y-3 mb-8">
    <li><code class="text-accent-light">gtl status --json</code> — full allocation details</li>
    <li><code class="text-accent-light">gtl routes --json</code> — routing URLs per port</li>
    <li><code class="text-accent-light">gtl doctor --json</code> — health diagnostics</li>
    <li><code class="text-accent-light">gtl env --json</code> — env file contents</li>
    <li><code class="text-accent-light">gtl resolve &lt;project&gt; --json</code> — another project's URL</li>
    <li><code class="text-accent-light">gtl start --await</code> — blocks until TCP accepts (with <code class="text-accent-light">--await-timeout</code>)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-4 scroll-mt-24 text-balance mt-14">Agent context file</h2>
  <p class="text-muted mb-10">
    <code class="text-accent-light">gtl install</code> writes an <code class="text-white">AGENTS.md</code> file with instructions for setup, teardown, and server management. Any MCP-compatible editor reads it as context. Cross-repo service URLs follow the same <code class="text-accent-light">gtl resolve</code> contract as humans.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-4 scroll-mt-24 text-balance mt-14">Read next</h2>
  <ul class="text-muted space-y-2 list-disc pl-5 mb-8">
    <li><a href="/features/agents/" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2">AI Agents feature page</a></li>
    <li><a href="/docs/agents/" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2">Docs: AI agent integration</a></li>
    <li><a href="/docs/resolve/" class="text-accent-light hover:text-accent underline underline-offset-2">Docs: Resolve guide</a></li>
  </ul>

  <p class="text-center">
    <a href="/use-cases/" class="text-sm text-accent-light hover:text-accent">All use cases</a>
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
